50|$|The {{film is a}} {{cooperative}} effort between Eurasia Motion Pictures (Canada), Spice Factory (UK), and Bjolfskvida (Iceland), and it was filmed in Iceland. The story {{takes place in the}} early half of the sixth century AD in what is now Denmark, but the filming of the movie in Iceland provided many panoramic views of that country's landscape. In 2006, a documentary of the making of Beowulf and Grendel, called <b>Wrath</b> <b>of</b> <b>Gods,</b> was released and went on to win six film awards in Europe and the U.S.|$|R
